  "name": "Blinding Foam",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You spray a colorful, caustic foam into the target's eyes, which clings to their face. Make a spell attack roll. If you hit, you deal @Damage[5d10[acid]] damage and @Damage[1d6[persistent,acid]] damage, and the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.XgEqL1kFApUbl5Z2]{Blinded} for the duration. The foam can be removed with 3 Interact actions, which ends the persistent acid damage. These Interact actions don't need to be consecutive. When the target's persistent acid damage ends, the spell automatically ends.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (8th)</strong> The initial damage increases to @Damage[9d10[acid]], and the persistent acid damage increases to @Damage[2d6[persistent,acid]].</p>"
    },
